12/08/2005
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The International Criminal Tribunal for the former Yugoslavia (ICTY) has decided on the status of 39 of the 86 cases of war crimes against Serbs, a spokesperson for Republika Srpska's ICTY co-operation and war crime investigation secretariat said Thursday (11 August). According to the spokesperson, Sanda Vukojevic, the ICTY labelled 42 persons as "A" -- suggesting that the evidence supports the accusations, and an indictment could be made. The court labelled 117 persons as "B", saying they could not be indicted based on the evidence. Another 89 individuals were categorized as "C", meaning that additional evidence was requested to support potential indictments. Vukojevic confirmed that all the cases not reviewed by the ICTY were transferred to the BiH court. (Nezavisne Novine - 12/08/05; RTRS, NTV Hayat - 11/08/05)
